It&#8217;s understood the accused was playing with a firearm when it went off and struck another boy in the face. JOHANNESBURG A 14-year-old Limpopo school boy has been arrested after he shot and killed another boy in Mankweng.Police say the teenager stole his uncle s firearm and went to attend extra mathematics class along with the deceased on Sunday.It s understood the accused was playing with the firearm when a bullet went off and struck another boy in the face. He was declared dead at the scene.The police s Mohlaka Mashiane says, The suspect has been taken to Bosasa, a juvenile prison, and we will open a case of murder. According to the information received, the uncle has been charged for the negligent handling of a firearm and he apparently doesn t have the proper licence to possess that firearm. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)